run some QA tests on the last $x commits, in a Koha git repo

1/ first, configure your shell vars correctly
    $ export KOHA_CONF=/path/to/your/koha/koha-conf.xml
    $ export PERL5LIB="${PERL5LIB}":\
            /path/to/your/koha.git:\
            /path/to/your/koha.git/C4/SIP

2/ copy perlcriticrc file to your home dir (important!)
    $ cp /path/to/your/koha-qa-tools/perlcriticrc ~/

3/ cd to your Koha git repo
    $ cd /path/to/your/koha.git

4/ apply a new patch to test
    $ git bz apply 4460

5/ run a qa-test on your Koha git repo, for the last commit
    $ koha-qa.pl -c 1



use -c to test the last $NUM of commits
    $ koha-qa.pl -c 5

use -v to change verbosity (default is 0)
    $ koha-qa.pl  -v 2
